    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Neovim bundles its dependencies and downloads their source by CMake. This is great in general. But in the homebrew, building path will always remain clean. This means 3rd-party's downloads will not be cached which is painful especially for repeating compiling for debug purpose.\n\n[Homebrew's policy](https://github.com/Homebrew/homebrew/blob/master/share/doc/homebrew/Acceptable-Formulae.md#we-dont-like-install-scripts-that-download-things) is let homebrew handle external resource's download. An example is [here](https://github.com/Homebrew/homebrew/blob/master/Library/Formula/ansible.rb).\n\nIt would increase developer's job a little. But compare to its advantage, it's worthy to do it.\n",
    "closed_at": "2014-11-07T13:50:13Z",
