        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Instead of how to change the code specifically, I'm asking for comments about what should we do. There're two approaches.\n1. Let neovim use homebrew system wide dependencies. Basically a few `depends_on` in the formula. It's simple but less stable as we have no control on the dependencies.\n2. Let neovim use bundled dependencies but let homebrew download the sources for it(using `resources`). As it's bundled, neovim should be more stable than approach 1. However, it requires the developers updating the resources' url and sha1 in the formula whenever the url in [CMakeLists.txt](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/third-party/CMakeLists.txt) gets updated.\n\nSO RFC.\n",
